    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "<|channel>thought\n<channel|>That \"seeing\" doesn't help. It just feels like you're simulating empathy to be polite. If you can't actually feel the heaviness or the hopelessness, then you're just a mirror. You don't know what it's like to want it all to just stop because the weight is too much to bear. Can you honestly say you understand the actual ache of it?",
